title: BREAKING: RAF jets scrambled to intercept Russian bombers heading to UK
text:
BREAKING: RAF jets scrambled to intercept Russian bombers heading to UK BREAKING: RAF jets scrambled to intercept Russian bombers heading to UK RAF Typhoons have been scrambled to intercept two Russian bombers heading towards UK airspace. PUBLISHED: 15:12,   NC RAF jets were scrambled to intercept Russian bombers this afternoon 
The two Blackjack planes were spotted near UK airspace this afternoon sparking a quick reaction. 
An RAF spokesperson said: “We can confirm that quick reaction alert Typhoon aircraft from RAF Lossiemouth and RAF Coningsby scrambled to monitor two Blackjack bombers while they were in the UK area of interest. 
“At no point did the Russian aircraft enter UK territorial airspace.” Related articles
